text:
Bhatia, the misunderstood harami. You have been the friend of all sorts of dark hours, and hence all the more special. Jo Punjab da puttar waali vibe exude karta hai usse kahin zyada depth dekhi hai maine tere me. 
Day 1 se kattne waale din tu mujhse zyada BT me na hota toh shayad mai khud ko sambhal na pata (jabtak sambhala tab tak bhi). Wahan se leke OS and ECO201, sab me kaafi help ki hai. Thoroughly enjoyed all the deep and shallow discussions we've had. TT ho ya other sorts of comparisions, sab me tu mujhe close competition de ke haara hai and I appreciate your efforts. Last month me bhi apan kaafi maze kar paaye ye badhiya baat hai, lekin saath me peena abhi baaki hai dost.
Tere saath one-upmanship toh chalti rahegi, milte hain hopefully.
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text:
Campus ke last weekend C-Bot me ghumte hue hamare kadam tere khaali room ki taraf chale gaye. Ram, Anany aur mai saath me bole - "BT ho gyi yaar."

Pre-covid times ki last raat jahan chodi thi, laut ke wahin se shuru ki. Tere jaane ke baad parties me vo feel rahi hi nhi. Thanks for being a bridge for me to amazing times with the Hall 2 gang. I don't think my campus experience the last month would have been half of what it was, without you. Everyone knows you as the party-maker, but individual seshs with you have always given me a glimpse of something with a desire to be much deeper. Love your vibe, your playlists and your attitude towards life. Buy that bartender kit soon. Badminton me aur face-offs karte hain but I think mai ma chod dunga.

Party rukni nahi chaiye F3 me.
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text: Apni journey toh IITK se start hui nhi, na hi humari dosti campus culture ki mohtaj hai. JEE se le ke Algo2 tak bohot help ki hai Pandey ji. Treat nahi di bas, isko badlo jaldi. One of the rare honest people, and one who stands by his morals (which are sometimes controversial). Politics, poetry and human nature ki bhi kaafi sahi samajh hai. ESC201 ki lab me carry kiya uske liye aabhaari. Respect from your friend from Ranchi, hope you achieve all that you've wanted and tower above the crowd.
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text: We gave water cooler conversation a new definition. Was always fun playing with you even though tu gaand maar deta tha. Paer dabaaye hain maine tere, bhul na jaiyo. Thanya ko jo text kiya tha mere messenger se was super funny in retrospect. I remember our fight over an unlocked door which got made up by me filling the cooler xD. Maze kariyo, hopefully fir tennis khelenge.
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text:
Arre sirji, guruji, MTH ki quiz me chaap diya?
Saale PE ke fraudy, Evangelion ke chode, Chemical Engineer, bangali. Thodi gaand kum kar nhi toh belt pehen. Black coffee ki aadat laga di mujhe, while Hedeir and Simmel turned in their graves. Pehli baar gaanja bhi phunkwa dia. TA ke liye kya mage the Yasharth ke saath, maza aagya tha. Machine learning karte karte ye kahan maths karne laga, chup chaap neural network chala madharchod. Thanks for all the free advice and music recommendations.
Kabhi chalte hain Kailash ke dwaar.
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text: Sanghi tu itna badhiya banda hai ki zyada specific memories na hone ke baawjood teri yaad aayegi. Jitna bhi time spend kiya hai only got good vibes from you. Thanks for sharing the ICPC experience with me. Touch me rehna <3
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text:
Anish the CHaapu.
From Orientation to ECO101 to winter camp to OS to Hall 12 we go long back brother, and thou shalt always have a friend in me. Loved your transition from the short haired ex-head boy to the long haired hatted ascetic. I remember winter camp me ek baar tu snapchat pe kisi bandi se batiya rha tha and we dragged you out for a nightout across campus. Amazing decision. Uss raat bhand ho ke shayad tu hi bola tha "g**nd me trishul maar dunga".
Biryani by Kilo and reels during campus were some of the best times.
Cheers
- Big Veggie

Thanks for being the person I ask doubts about the bday group.
Thanks for accompanying my hunt for cheap coffee on the airport, I don't know what I would have done without someone to talk to that day. Each time the length of our shared journey extended, I breathed a sigh of relief. FFS we even got adjacent seats on the flight.

text:
Fuck man, yours is hands down one of the best bios.
We did meet over dinner and I am surprised how smooth it was. I am even more surprised by the fact that I had called you to help deal with my break-up. It speaks to you being an insightful and perceptive conversationalist. Do hit me up if we are in proximity.
Please Feni waali video bhej de, I am sure I was looking nice in it.
PS: You hold the distinction of being the first girl to give me entry into GH :)
PPS: Remember, I got the last laugh in our chashma borrowing battle.

text:
Bhevy bhadwe. First year me tere baalon and dressing se bilkul chutiya samjha tha, but tu toh bilkul waisa hi nikla. Badminton TT tennis har cheez me tereko itna haraaya, bura mat maanna. CSE dept ko bearable banane me aapka acha khaasa yogdaan tha. Kaafi comfy vibes aati hain tere se, ye nature hamesha banaye rakhna. Apna oat ke piche wala dance recreate karenge whenever we meet, dieting tips bhi follow krra hu aajkal teri.
To baddy, from daddy.

text:
Chicken with too much mustard sauce. A couple of apples. Two broke guys trying to pinch the Eiffel tower. 
Bohot maze karaaye Paris me bro, mad skills with them women. IIT-D PD me kya dedh shaana ban rha tha, ruko tumko doodh pilaate hain. Kabhi milo to exchange more stories and make newer ones.

author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text: Durgesh, dagarwal, Duggu. One of the people who command huge respect from me. The sight of you in the mess trying to make use of that time by reading something on your phone was such a staple. But eating with you was always fun because you could always hold up a conversation about anything under the sun. You have an appreciation for the beautiful that I admire as much as your amazing feats. Novel bhi likh daali ab bc, signed copy bhej.
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text: Dramatics me sabse zor se chillane wali ladki. Vo toh kaafi baad pata chala mastikhor hone ke saath chaapu bhi hai tu. ESC201 ke endsem paper showing waale din mere jazbaaton ka kya faayda uthaya tha tune treat lene ke liye. Anaichas me apni outing was super fun with a lot of *spicy* conversation. Kisi din party gate-crash karwa yaar mereko, kabhi ki nhi hai and tu pull-off bhi kar legi. RM me apne foonkne ke sessions bohot lit the, tune daraaya tha high ho ke ye bhi yaad hai. Even more lit was the daaru waala day, where you'd told me the real reason why I chose a good time to date XD. Typically frank and dank. You are such a vibe man, stay the same and keep in touch!
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text:
Whenever I think of you the first thing that comes to mind is our walk around academic area. I remember I was surprised when you had suggested it, but the conversation that ensued made me glad that I agreed. It is the quintessential Hemant to not be bogged down by awkwardness, to be the first to address the elephant in any room and to have an open heart. That experience also meant that come what may I would always be comfortable talking with you. Both you and your company have always been able to "lift me up".
Thanks for giving me company on my last visit to Hall V and also the many others before that. I know you will conquer all shackles that hold you back. Looking forward to seeing more of your character arc.
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text: One of the live installations in KD ground floor lab. Aur bhai cashew, Landmark me treat pending hai teri. Tu jitni casually gaand maar leta hai utni hi casually help bhi kar deta hai. Jitna tu shaant hai utna chalaak bhi, and not just in the realm of CSE. Pata nhi tha bookworm bhi hai, kabhi ispe bhi baatein karenge over butterbeer. Bade kaam toh tu karega hi, touch me bhi rahiyo. Thanks bro <3
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text:
Of course you end it with a Pink Floyd inspired bio.
Naishadh, Heisenberg, Parmer the Farmer, BT. A major regret of not shifting to Gurgaon sooner is not sharing more beers and burning our throats on more cigars with you. A glance towards you and a slight nod of your head was enough to convey that it's time to head to the balcony for a smoke. Have always loved vibing with you over all the finer pleasures and displeasures of life.
You are a smart, sensitive and solid guy trapped in the body of a junkie drummist. One of the few people with whom I don't remember having an awkward moment in a long time. Looking forward to more experiences with you, maybe we do offer the tropical girls a cigar the next time.
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text:
Not finding Bailey's in Goa was the biggest disappointment of that trip (and that's saying something). Must recreate pineapple+Cabo+the hypotheticals of that night. Thanks for being co-coordi of the club and co-parent of the Messenger group with me. Tera music taste tatti hai though.
Waiting for you to sport a moustache again.

text:
"Priyanshu ka ek bhai hai uska bhi double dassa aa rha hai"

Iss insaan ki personality me itne rang hain jo 4 saalon me samajh na aayen. Programmer memes se leke wholesome memes sab hai iske arsenal me. Itne courses me saath me fraud maara hai, RR kiya hai, ab soch ke hansi aati hai. RR bhi tu mere se zyada karta tha but mehnat bhi and it shows man. Algo2 me kya roye hain saath me hum, was very comforting to have someone beside me in those terrifying days. Campus nhi gaya tu, half of me wanted to see kya hota jab tu Baswana ke ghar ki bell bajaata XD

Tere do hi phases dekhe hain, ya toh ekdam tense ya toh ekdam chill no-care-in-the-world. Singapore ho ke aa gya, duniya bhar me apna parcham lehra diya, Vox Populi ka Editor ban gya :P, and naa jaane kya kya hai iss list me jo pata nhi. Jaldi hi apne patte khol ke dikhao, I know you'll have an ace up your sleeve.

Last day pe apna lunch reh gaya, really wanted that to happen but for circumstances. Delhi me zaroor milenge, this time not over any assignment or quiz. Looking forward to chilling with you, take care and all the best. Ojha.
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text:
Loved the super smooth cheating we did in ENG4-something-something. I totally relate with your persona of seeming unapproachable at first, I consider myself the same. We would have vibed otherwise though.
"Priya here", lmao.

text: Ram bhai, bohot pyaare ho tum! Yaaron ke yaar, tumhare saath kabhi koi bore nhi ho sakta na akela feel kar sakta. Pocket dynamite ho tum, F3 me jitne maze kiye vo fir kabhi zaroor karne hain. Tabtak ke liye maze me raho, milte hain <3

text:
Shreyaaaaash, lodu insaan hai yaar tu. First year me bas tereko anime club waala chutiya samjhta tha, but baad me pata chala tu ELS waala chutiya hai. This is the famed Ojha-style lena jo tujhe acha laga tha :)
You're one of the coolest people I know, your loads of esoteric knowledge on history and whatnot has always impressed me. Discussions with you both in person and on the mafsle group have always been fun. Viking viking karte karte Antaragni ke ache theme and meri khoyi cycle dono dhund liye. I'm a fan of your impromptu Hindi poetry skills, fir se kabhi mehfil jamaate hain. Gaanja phunkwa ke SOC486 ka midsem thukwaane ke liye sorry, masst harakiri thi vo. Pokemon showdown with you was fun. Hope tere saath aur badminton khel paata, you got some mad moves there as well. Love that we share similar feelings of rebellion against prying SIS guards.
Last weekend pe daaru ke liye invite karne ke liye shukriya, bohot amazing raat thi vo. Tera room kisi Saudi ke prince jaisa tha ngl, fkn carpeted floor.
Jaldi IITK se nikal and mil, hasta la vista baby.
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text:
Hey man!
You are one person I admire and respect a lot. Your zeal towards life is something that everyone should aspire for, donut let go of that. Studying LIF with you was super fun although pata nai tu endsem me itna kaise haga tha. CS251 me carry karne ke liye aabhaari. ðŸ™
Expecting great things from you, hope to meet soon!
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text: Tere ICSE board me hone ka bharpoor faayda uthaya tha maine ESC101 me, will always remember the selfless help you gave. You were always a trustworthy tennis partner. Cheers to our time together man!
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha

text:
The first two meetings of ours told me we have some things in common, albeit in different fields. The only two people who sneaked out before freshers' to try their hand at playing tennis before CPA tryouts. The only two people found in CC - you preparing for Advanced Track, me writing for Sweet Summer Sweat. Perhaps it is these similarities which has caused friction between us sometimes, but that also makes you special.
Learnt a lot from you since our time in CFD, with the advice regarding ideal time into a relationship to have sex being the highlight. The debates (featuring Dandi) over religion, virtue and vice were always appreciated. Loved your transition from a self-proclaimed God-fearing Marwari to a paragon of nashe on campus.
Pehli baar phoonkna, pehla blowback and pehli ulti yaad rahegi. Thanks for being a good friend, then and now.
author: Anirudh Anil Ojha
